                            <comment id="17168899" author="paulk" created="Fri, 31 Jul 2020 14:32:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Turns out there&apos;s not as obvious a fix as you might first think:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;while there was no Groovy syntax pre-Parrot which used the initializer expressions, they could be added programmatically as is done in MarkupBuilderCodeTransformer, and such code would be looking for null for the sizeExpression currently if an initializer is used, so changing it could break code&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the plural &quot;getExpressions&quot; vs non-plural &quot;getSizeExpression&quot; inconsistency is also messy to change - though we could introduce aliases and deprecate the original - in some sense either could work - it is in fact an &quot;initializer&quot; expression (singular) consisting of the list of individual expressions (plural)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;For now I have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;added a &lt;tt&gt;hasInitializer()&lt;/tt&gt; method so that whether a null or empty list is used for sizeExpression can remain a hidden internal detail&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;clarified the javadoc comments to make the naming inconsistency a little easier to comprehend&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="17169186" author="daniel_sun" created="Fri, 31 Jul 2020 22:36:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The proposed PR is merged. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
